job_description:
Job Description

Our Debt Advisory team supports organisations to make sound financial and capital structuring decisions. We work closely with our clients to provide independent advice on financing options and strategy and then support their capital raising activities in the market, including preparation of supporting materials and direct negotiations with financiers.

Our Debt Advisory team focuses on providing independent financial advisory services and financing options across a range of transactions, including (amongst others):

- Medium to large corporate borrowers seeking to raise, refinance or consider options for raising debt.
- Project finance transactions across the mining, infrastructure and energy industries.
- Securitisation, non-bank issuers and financial services companies
- Advice for government related organisations associated with debt or debt-like instruments.Our team has the capability to deliver funding solutions from multiple capital providers including bank and non-bank lenders, and we are heavily involved in the preparation of supporting materials and direct negotiations with financiers to support our clients’ capital raising activities in the market.

Your Opportunity – Analyst / Executive 

The ideal candidate will bring a strong attention to detail, have strong numeracy skills, a strong skillset with the Microsoft Office suite of products (in particular PowerPoint and Excel) and will support the team’s national strategy by:

- Demonstrating enthusiasm for, or recent experience in, a corporate finance, financial advisory or deals-based environment.
- Applying your corporate finance or commercial experiences across a broad range of capital products and situations.
- The ability to develop financial models and provide financial analysis of your modelling.
- Providing financial analysis for complex transactions across a variety of sectors.
- Supporting the delivery of transactions and interacting with clients, financiers, and legal advisors.
- Identifying issues, generating options, and supporting our recommendations to clients.
- Assisting with the preparation of engagement deliverables including funding options reports, teaser documents, information memorandums, financial models, term sheets and other detailed PowerPoint reports and presentations.The KPMG Debt Advisory team sits within Corporate Finance, working shoulder to shoulder with our M&A colleagues, and is part of our larger national Deal Advisory & Infrastructure group. This group is dedicated to assisting clients to find and drive value throughout the deal and transformation lifecycle, from strategy through to deal execution and post deal implementation.

Our Debt Advisory team are part of our global KPMG network, with the ability to derive global industry insights, research, and market data as well leveraging client relationships in various geographies.

How are you extraordinary?

- You have a strong interest in debt markets and funding options for organisations and their projects.
- You enjoy working in flexible environments and are positive with your communication skills in a team-based environment.
- You are strong at analysing and telling stories with information.
- You are comfortable in preparing high-quality presentations and marketing materials.
- You enjoy working in the detail, with a proactive attitude towards accuracy and deadlines.
- You can work autonomously in a teams-based environment, where you can readily multitask and work with limited information to determine the optimal outcome.Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background, and experience, strengthens relationships, and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients, and communities. To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills, and experience could include:

- Experience or a strong interest in financial advisory in a professional services environment.
- Experience in a banking environment (e.g., credit analyst) .
- Suitable tertiary qualifications. Completion, or in progress, of relevant post-graduate studies (e.g., CFA) will be viewed favourably.
- Communication, report writing and presentation skills suitable for client / marketing delivery.
- An appetite and enthusiasm for corporate finance with a work ethic and a motivation to achieve best outcomes for clients, KPMG, and yourself.
- Quantitative and qualitative analytical skills to support client & project data needs.
- A team mindset with a willingness to learn, attention to detail and the ability to work to timelines.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

We are recruiting for a Research Analyst to join the highly regarded Australian Small Caps Research team at Associate level. This is an excellent opportunity for someone with a strong quantitative skillset, excellent communication skills and a passion for learning to work in an exciting and fast-paced job that will help to accelerate your career. This position offers meaningful autonomy, to build out coverage and gain exposure to a broad range of industries and business models and engage directly with key corporate executives and client decision makers.

Responsibilities

- Creating and maintaining earnings models by leveraging skills in accounting, finance and economics
- Researching and writing reports with a company or sector specific focus
- Developing relationships and interacting with equity sales and trading, institutional clients, investor relations personnel, company management and other industry participants 
- Collaborating with domestic, regional and global colleagues on research projects 
- Idea generation – finding insights and actionable value-add for clients
- Discovery – exploring the under-researched stocks that can “move the needle” for small cap investors

Qualifications

Skills Required 

- A university degree or post-graduate qualification (or equivalent), demonstrating advanced numeracy and exceptional communication skills
- Deep curiosity and a passion for learning
- Aptitude to think laterally, creatively and to problem solve
- Ability to work in small teams, with a strong focus on coordination, collaboration and teamwork
- Adaptable approach, with the capability to cover multiple industries and business models 
- Proactive and hard-working, with a willingness to work independently, to meet deadlines and take accountability
- Previous experience in financial services, with a proven skillset in constructing financial models 

What You Can Expect From Morgan Stanley

We are committed to maintaining the first-class service and high standard of excellence that have defined Morgan Stanley for over 89 years. Our values - putting clients first, doing the right thing, leading with exceptional ideas, committing to diversity and inclusion, and giving back - aren’t just beliefs, they guide the decisions we make every day to do what's best for our clients, communities and more than 80,000 employees in 1,200 offices across 42 countries. At Morgan Stanley, you’ll find an opportunity to work alongside the best and the brightest, in an environment where you are supported and empowered. Our teams are relentless collaborators and creative thinkers, fueled by their diverse backgrounds and experiences. We are proud to support our employees and their families at every point along their work-life journey, offering some of the most attractive and comprehensive employee benefits and perks in the industry. There’s also ample opportunity to move about the business for those who show passion and grit in their work.

To learn more about our offices across the globe, please copy and paste https://www.morganstanley.com/about-us/global-offices into your browser.

Morgan Stanley’s goal is to build and maintain a workforce that is diverse in experience and background but uniform in reflecting our standards of integrity and excellence. Consequently, our recruiting efforts reflect our desire to attract and retain the best and brightest from all talent pools. We want to be the first choice for prospective employees.

It is the policy of the Firm to ensure equal employment opportunity without discrimination or harassment on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, age, sex, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, citizenship, disability, marital and civil partnership/union status, pregnancy (including unlawful discrimination on the basis of a legally protected pregnancy/maternity leave), veteran status, genetic information, or any other characteristic protected by law.

Morgan Stanley is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversifying its workforce.

Collins Executive Recruitment has been exclusively mandated to appoint a Junior Analyst to join a high-performing private equity fund with a proven track record in growth-stage investing.
The OpportunityThe fund invests in founder-led technology and software businesses with established product-market fit and growth potential. Its strategy combines long-term capital with active partnership, working closely with management teams to accelerate growth, scale operations, and unlock strategic value.
This position offers unique exposure to the entire investment lifecycle, from origination and due diligence through to portfolio value creation and exit. You will work directly with experienced investment professionals in a dynamic and entrepreneurial environment.
The RoleAs a Junior Analyst, you will support investment origination, execution, and portfolio management across a pipeline of innovative technology and software businesses. The role requires intellectual curiosity, analytical rigour, and initiative, with an emphasis on independent thinking in a lean, high-performance setting.
Key Responsibilities:
- Conduct detailed financial, commercial, and strategic analysis of prospective investments.
- Support due diligence processes, including market mapping, competitor benchmarking, and operational assessments.
- Build and maintain robust financial models to guide investment decisions.
- Prepare investment memoranda, presentations, and supporting materials for internal committees.
- Engage with portfolio company executives to assist in strategic and operational value creation initiatives.
- Monitor portfolio performance, highlighting risks, opportunities, and growth drivers.
- Contribute to investment pipeline development through proactive research and industry coverage.
Candidate Profile
- Up to 2 years’ professional experience in finance, consulting, accounting, investment management, corporate development, technology, engineering, or a related field.
- Strong academic record with a degree in Finance, Business, Economics, IT, Engineering, or a related discipline (Distinction/High Distinction average).
- Advanced analytical and problem-solving skills.
- Clear and confident communication skills, with the ability to engage senior stakeholders.
- A self-starter with the maturity to operate in an agile and less structured environment.
- Demonstrated passion for technology and software, and a clear ambition to build a career in investment.
Why JoinThis is an opportunity to fast-track your career in private equity, gaining hands-on experience in complex transactions and value creation. You will join a collaborative, ambitious team that prizes curiosity, accountability, and creativity, while providing direct exposure to senior investment professionals and portfolio executives.

Company Description

Lendi Group is a market-leading digital platform business focused on transforming the home loan industry. It operates the country’s #1 retail mortgage broker – the iconic Aussie Home Loans franchise – and the Australia’s #1 digital mortgage brand, Lendi.

Together, with its national network of 1,300 brokers and 230 retail stores, the Lendi Group brands give all Australians the power of choice, and confidence, in one of life’s biggest financial decisions.

Building on this market-leading foundation, Lendi Groups vision is to be the undisputed place for Australians to buy and own property through our new Aussie Homes propositions.

Lendi Group’s loan book is more than $100b and it was named Australia’s Aggregator of the Year for 2024

Diversity, Equality, and Inclusion are fundamental to the success of Lendi Group. We’re passionate about fostering an environment where our team members feel valued and supported and we celebrate everyone’s unique identity.

To learn more about life at Lendi Group check out our blog: https://www.lendi.com.au/inspire/category/life-at-lendi/

About the role? 

Learn fast. Think big. Turn data into decisions that make a difference.

As an Analyst in Lendi Group’s Data Supergroup, you’ll help power our journey to become an AI native organisation. You’ll work closely with senior analysts, data scientists, and business stakeholders to transform data into insights that drive smarter, faster decisions across the business.

You’ll support the design, development, and maintenance of Power BI dashboards, reports, and curated datasets that deliver trusted intelligence to teams across Product, Distribution, Finance, and Executive functions. Your work will help ensure our leaders have the data they need to guide strategy, improve performance, and enhance customer experiences.

This role is perfect for someone early in their analytics career who is curious, detail-oriented, and passionate about learning how to turn data into business impact. You’ll gain hands-on experience with modern data tools and AI-powered analytics, from SQL and Python to GPT-based assistants and anomaly detection systems.

If you’re ready to grow your skills, contribute to high-impact projects, and learn from some of the best in data, this is your opportunity to help shape the future of analytics at Lendi Group.

Job Description

Analytics & Reporting

- Assist in building and maintaining Power BI dashboards, reports, and datasets using tools such as SQL, Python, and dbt.
- Perform data exploration and analysis to uncover trends and insights that support key business initiatives.
- Support data modelling and transformation within cloud environments such as Snowflake to ensure data accuracy and reliability.

AI Native Enablement

- Learn to use GPT-based tools and autonomous agents to assist with natural language querying and insight generation.
- Support automated reporting and anomaly detection initiatives that improve efficiency and insight delivery.

Stakeholder Engagement

- Collaborate with Product, Distribution, Finance, and Executive teams to respond to data requests and deliver recurring insights.
- Help translate data findings into clear, simple visualisations and summaries that support decision-making across the business.

Data Stewardship

- Contribute to documentation of business logic, data definitions, and KPI frameworks.
- Support the team in promoting data quality, consistency, and governance across reporting assets.

Qualifications

- 1-3 years’ experience in analytics, business intelligence, or data-related roles (graduates with relevant experience encouraged to apply).
- Working knowledge of SQL with some exposure to Python and Power BI.
- Familiarity with or interest in cloud data warehouses such as Snowflake is advantageous.
- Strong analytical mindset and attention to detail, with the ability to identify patterns and insights in data.
- Effective communicator who can translate data into simple, actionable insights for non-technical audiences.
- Eagerness to learn modern analytics practices, including AI-powered and automated reporting tools.
- Experience or interest in financial services, technology, or real estate is highly regarded.

Additional Information

Lendi Group teams operate across Australia and the Philippines. We’re committed to creating a new era of seamless connection in property finance by changing the way Australians experience property lending, for good.

A few of the benefits that our people rave about include:

- A vibrant, relaxed, yet professional culture
- Holistic wellbeing programs offering 24/7 support, including medical, mental health, and financial wellbeing services to enable our workforce to thrive at home and work
- Generous Paid Parental Leave: we celebrate our growing Lendi Group family with 18-26 weeks leave for primary carers and up to 4 weeks for secondary carers
- An additional week’s Loyalty Leave each year after reaching 3 years of service
- Wellness initiatives with a strong focus on psychological safety
- Social groups such as our industry-leading Women in Technology group.

Our culture is guided by our 3 core values: We Are Stronger United; Act Like You Own It; and Keep Home Loans Human. Our values are part of our core DNA that helps Lendi Group to attract, engage and evolve the right talent and build best-in-class products.

Feeling like you don’t meet all the skills listed? That’s ok; we are always on the lookout for different skills, experience, and qualities and so we’d still like to hear from you.

job_description:
Job Description

We are looking Project Analyst to join our Delivery team in Sydney. Reporting to Head of Delivery, the Project Analyst is responsible for supporting the delivery of assigned projects and managing the day to day aspect of project lifecycle to ensure the prescribed scope is delivered to the agreed budget, schedule and quality.

This role requires interaction with a diverse range of internal and external stakeholders, most often managing several moving project parts simultaneously.

Project management responsibilities revolve around delivering every project on time within budget and scope.

Qualifications

What you'll need to succeed:

- Minimum 1- 2 years’ experience in Project Coordination.
- Tertiary education in a related field.
- Familiar with Atlassian suite (JIRA, Confluence), whiteboarding tool, such as MIRO, Lucid, Project Management tooling (MS Project, Monday) is an ideal.
- Software Development industry experiences are desirable.
- Have good collaborative working style that drives customer focus and great project engagement.
- Self-starter who think outside the box and challenge the status-quo.
- Have a growth mindset and contribute to our continuous improvement culture
- You have good written and verbal communication skills
- You have good attention to detail
- Conflict resolution skills

What's it like to work here?

As a Symbion, you have flexibility to shape when, where and how you work. Symbions can choose to be primarily remote, primarily office-based, or a mix of both.

You also have the freedom to shape your development. Every Symbion is able to design a unique and customised learning journey to build new skills and reach career goals.

Plus, you’ll enjoy a range of benefits including share options, generous parental leave, regular social events, social clubs and a comfortable, fun and diverse working environment.

If this sounds like the next great step in your career, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply Now!

Symbio is an equal opportunity employer. All applications will be treated with the strictest confidentiality. You will need to have current work rights to work in Australia and be prepared to undergo relevant background checks. No recruiters please.

Additional Information

Life at Symbio

We ensure our employees have equal access to a range of learning and development opportunities, and encourage everyone, regardless of gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation or life stage to embrace these opportunities, enabling them to develop themselves and their career.

Our employee’s happiness, health and wellbeing is important at Symbio. We provide all employees with flexible working options to ensure that work doesn’t compromise life outside Symbio and also supports their wellbeing. We regularly enhance our employee benefits such as discounted Aussie Broadband internet, up to 26 weeks paid parental leave including super contributions for primary and secondary carers and social clubs.

At Symbio, our diverse backgrounds and unique experiences allow us to continue to innovate and create the brands, networks and technologies to power the future of global communications.

Salary Range: Band 4 $ 89,207 - $ 95,764 + Superannuation

(Remuneration stated is for the full-time positions)

Work type: Temporary Full-time

Duration: Up to 12 months (07/02/2026 – 05/02/2027) with potential for future opportunities at Council

Location: Brisbane Square

Number of roles: 2

Ready to shape the future of Brisbane? Your journey starts here.

Are you a recent graduate driven by purpose and passionate about creating meaningful change? Do you dream of contributing to projects that matter—projects that shape the city around you and leave a lasting legacy?

A graduate position with Council is more than just a job. It’s your launchpad to:

- kick-start a meaningful career with one of Australia's most influential local governments. 
- grow through our extended training program, designed to support your development and help you achieve your future goals
- make a difference by helping deliver a better Brisbane—one that’s vibrant, inclusive, and ready for the world stage
- as a Council graduate, you could help shape the infrastructure, culture, and community spirit that will define Brisbane for generations to come. This is your chance to be part of something historic. 

Your future starts now. Your city needs you.

What can I expect from this program? 

- one year program
- exposure and experience aligned to your studies
- engage in group and one-on-one development initiatives
- mentorship
- rotational based placements. 

The Role 

We have 2 opportunities for Graduate Business Analysts to work across Council. These roles will help to inform decision making, finding solutions and creating great outcomes for the benefit of residents and visitors of Brisbane. Developing and maintaining reports, working with business analysis, Power BI, sharing knowledge, developing steps to improve processes and results, and looking at trends and areas for change will see you reach meaningful conclusions whilst learning and developing every day.

Our Purpose

Brisbane City Council is the largest local government in Australia with an annual budget of $4.1 billion, more than 9,000 employees and providing a broad range of services including planning and development, traffic management, public transport, roads, bikeways, paths, parks, bridges, festivals, community facilities and cemeteries.

Council’s diverse and inclusive workforce helps make Brisbane a great place to live, work and relax. As a values-based organisation, Council takes immense pride in providing services of a high standard for those who live, work, study and visit Brisbane. Working in Council means delivering excellent customer service to the people of Brisbane.

To apply for the Graduate program, eligibility requires you to:

- hold a recognised degree or post graduate qualification from a tertiary institution, completed within the last two years OR be completing a recognised degree or postgraduate degree from a tertiary institution which will confer prior to commencement in the program in January 2026
- have visa/work rights that allow full-time work for the duration of the 12-month program. 

Benefits of working for Council include: 

- flexible working hours, and flexible arrangements
- free gym and wellness centre
- award winning superannuation fund
- generous leave provisions
- competitive salary. 

Benefits of working for Council: CLICK HERE

How to apply:  Click on the 'I’m interested' button to complete your online application. Please upload your tailored resume and covering letter (of no more than one page) demonstrating your suitability to the position.

This role may require a Criminal History Check, or you may be required to undertake a pre-employment medical assessment to assess your ability to perform the genuine occupational requirements of the role.

For more information: Please email Karen Bishop on karen.bishop2@brisbane.qld.gov.au

People from diverse backgrounds, including those living with a disability and/or Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, who may have questions about the recruitment process or working at Council, are encouraged to reach out to the contact above, who can connect you with a member of Council’s Diversity and Inclusion team.

Application Closing Date: Sunday 19th October 2025 at 11:55pm AEST.

Brisbane City Council is a multi-award winning accessible and inclusive workplace where our people represent the diverse communities we serve, are supported, and can feel safe. Council has been awarded Employer of the Year at the National Disability Awards and has been recognised multiple times with ‘Gold Employer’ status from the Australian Workplace Equality Index for LGBTI inclusion.

About AV: Australian Vintage (AV) is an ASX-listed company and the proud owner of the multi-award-winning McGuigan, Tempus Two, Nepenthe, and Barossa Valley Wine Company brands. Leveraging our world-class assets and innovative expertise, we are dedicated to delivering exceptional results.
As a certified B Corporation, Australian Vintage is committed to making a positive impact on both people and the planet through continuous improvement and by using business as a force for good. We have set an ambitious Net Zero 2040 emissions target, are powered by renewable energy, and ensure all our owned and operated vineyards and wineries are certified under Sustainable Wine guidelines.
We support our people to make an impact where they live through paid volunteer days and are proud to be recognised as an accredited Mental Health First Aid workplace by Mental Health First Aid Australia as of January 2023.
About the role: This is a great opportunity for someone looking to grow their career in finance, analytics, or FMCG. As a Commercial Analyst, you will work closely with our Sales and Commercial teams to provide insights that make a real difference to the business. It is a hands-on role where you will learn a broad range of commercial functions – from pricing and forecasting through to financial reporting and sales analysis.
You will be part of a supportive team, gain exposure to senior stakeholders, and develop your skills in a fast-paced and exciting industry. No two days will look the same, and you will have plenty of opportunity to learn and grow.
What you’ll do:
- Support pricing and customer rebate processes, making sure customers are looked after quickly
- Prepare weekly sales reports and keep product and price information accurate and up to date
- Assist with monthly reporting and analysis to track performance against budgets and forecasts
- Contribute to forecasting and planning alongside Sales, Supply Chain and Finance
- Provide ad-hoc analysis and insights to help the team make smarter decisions
What you’ll bring:
- A degree in Accounting, Finance, Business, or a related field
- Strong Excel skills and a passion for working with data
- Attention to detail and a curious, problem-solving mindset
- Great communication skills and the ability to work well with others
- A desire to learn, develop, and build your career in FMCG and commercial analytics
- Experience with PowerBI is a bonus, but not essential
What we offer: We're proud to offer a strong benefits package that we know can make a big difference to work life and life outside of work.
- Primary carer parental leave offering 26 weeks paid leave
- Loyalty leave
- Work from Anywhere benefit, offering flexibility to work remotely
- Birthday leave
- Volunteer days
- Further education and study support
- Flexible working
- Mental health and wellbeing training and support
- Annual product allowance
- Options to purchase additional annual leave
- Sabbaticals and career breaks
- Continuation of superannuation while on paid and unpaid parental leave
If you are eager to build your career, enjoy working with data, and want to be part of a global wine business where your work has real impact, apply now.

About Us
With a small team of smart people who like working hard and have fun too, we released the most disruptive enterprise management software in the world: Odoo. Fully open source, full-featured with apps like Accounting, HR, CRM, Manufacturing, and 4,000 more. Its online offer is 3 times more affordable than traditional competitors like SAP and Microsoft.
Start a career with us. We offer you an extraordinary chance to learn and grow. Be involved with a very exciting product and a great team behind it.
Responsibilities
Join a vibrant and innovative team, working within an organisation that values independence, flexibility and personal growth. We are looking for Project Leaders to join our team responsible for ERP implementation projects. As a Project Leader, you will be the single point of contact for customers / clients, leading a project from beginning to end. You will be joining our Australian office based in Varsity Lakes, Gold Coast.
Your role will involve but not limited to:

- Analysing customer’s needs and business requirements
- Suggesting business flows before implementing agreed upon solutions
- Managing projects from A to Z, onboarding users on time and on budget
- Implementing our Odoo business software and deliver tailor-made training
- Steadily growing your expertise to provide customers with functional assistance
- Collaborating with Odoo's developers to execute specific customers' business requirements, as well as working with sales team in pre & post-sales
- Supporting the growth of our partner network to become Odoo experts
What's great about the job?

- A full-time position with attractive salary package and office benefits
- The opportunity to evolve with a great and fast-growing multinational company
- Get full responsibility on your projects
- Evolve quickly and learn a lot
- Explore large business scopes: CRM, manufacturing, accounting, inventory, HR, project management,...
- Coordinate with other Odoo departments: sales, developers, R&D,...
- Work with heaps of different customers and industries
- Coffee, tea, fruits and snacks provided at all times
MUST HAVE 🎯

- Permanent working rights in Australia
- Superior English
- Bachelor degree or higher
- At ease with software & IT
- Excellent analysis and communication skills
NICE TO HAVE ⭐

- 1-3 years of relevant experience
- Immediate availability
- Genuine interest in software & IT
CHALLENGES 🏋🏽 ♀️

- Master a complex product
- Deal with various industries
- A lot to learn

job_description:
Experienced working with Product Teams and providing insights and analysis on customer behaviour? Join Easygo in a newly created role working on our KICK platform!

What's in it for you?
As the Product Analyst for KICK you will play an important role within the Business Intelligence Team to help shape Product analytics for the KICK platform.Your role with us:
You will partner closely with the Product Teams to analyse and provide insights on how users interact with the KICK website and app. The Product Analyst will translate product questions into clear metrics and intuitive dashboard, while highlighting trends across features and funnels. You will uncover friction points, behavioural patterns and growth opportunities; providing concise, actionable readouts that drive smarter product decisions and shape the future of live streaming.Who are we?
At Easygo we proudly stand as a prominent service provider to a powerhouse of brands within the iGaming industry, including Stake.com, Kick.com and Twist Gaming. Stake is the world's largest crypto casino, and leads the industry with a seamless online casino and sportsbook experience. Level up your online entertainment with Kick.com, the vibrant live streaming platform, which connects millions of gamers and content creators worldwide. All alongside the innovative game design studio, Twist Gaming, which takes creativity to new heights by crafting cutting-edge and captivating games. Our commitment to placing our clients and their communities' entertainment at the forefront of everything we do, has solidified us as the ultimate online service provider for entertainment companies. Headquartered in the beautiful city of Melbourne, our growth has been remarkable. From humble beginnings to a thriving workforce of 600+, we've expanded not only in numbers but in ambition. There really is something for everyone here, whether you work in Tech, Marketing, Operations, Mathematics or Design, we are sure to have something for everyone.Click play on your career today!What you will do: 
- Manage end-to-end product analytics projects, from problem definition to delivering actionable solutions.
- Analyse how creators and viewers interact with the platform to identify behavioural patterns, friction points and opportunities for growth.
- Build, analyse and optimise A/B testing frameworks and other experiments to measure the impact of new features on engagement, retention, and monetisation.
- Assess the impact of product features, platform changes and community tools on core KPIs.
- Deliver fast, concise, decision-ready readouts to close the loop on product questions.
- Actively contribute to roadmap conversations by highlighting data-driven opportunities, risks and trade-oﬀs.
- Leverage a strong understanding of the live streaming ecosystem, creators and fann communities to contextualise trends and guide product strategy.
- Build, own and maintain dashboards for the Product team and leadership.
- Document data workflows, maintain metric definitions and dashboard guides and ensure clarity across fast-evolving features.
- Monitor reporting accuracy and freshness (e.g., schema changes, null spikes, metric drift) and escalate issues when needed.
- Maintain a high level of attention to detail and data quality across all analyses.
- Partner with Product Managers to define success metrics for creator tools, monetisation features and community engagement initiatives.
- Collaborate with BI and Data Science teams to build data assets, support machine learning models (e.g., recommendation systems) and improve tracking coverage.
- Clearly and compellingly communicate insights, acting as a bridge between Product, BI, and Engineering.
- Coach Product Managers on instrumentation, metric interpretation and dashboard best practices.What you will bring:
- 2+ years’ in Product Analytics/Data Analytics, preferably on event data analysis. 
- Demonstrated expertise in web and app analytics, including funnels, retention, engagement and cohort analysis. 
- Strong SQL skills and experience working with large datasets.
- Proficiency with modern BI tools (Looker, Tableau, Power BI or similar) and dashboard design best practices.

About UsFinsure is a premier mortgage aggregation company renowned for setting the benchmark in innovative financial solutions in Australia. We leverage cutting-edge technology and data analytics to empower our clients and lead the market. Our dynamic work culture celebrates innovation, embraces challenges, and focuses on delivering data-driven outcomes that add real business value.
Role OverviewDo you love turning data into insights that drive real business decisions? Join us as a Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst and make a direct impact by shaping how data informs strategy across the organisation.We are looking for someone who can do more than just build reports. This is a role for someone who can think strategically, understand business challenges, and create analytics solutions that empower the business to make better decisions.While many can produce dashboards, we need someone who can ask the right questions, connect the dots, and tell the story behind the data. This role will report directly to the Business Intelligence Lead and will play a key part in driving actionable insights across the organisation.
Key Responsibilities
- Deliver actionable insights: Translate complex data into clear findings that directly inform business decisions.
- Build high-impact reporting solutions: Design, develop, and maintain dashboards and reports that focus on the right metrics, not just more metrics.
- Manage ad hoc requests: Handle day-to-day data and reporting needs from multiple business units with speed and accuracy.
- SQL development and troubleshooting: Write, optimise, and debug SQL queries to extract and validate data, identify gaps, and resolve issues in existing queries or datasets.
- Partner with the business: Engage with stakeholders across different departments to understand their priorities and deliver analytics solutions that address real business needs.
- Ensure data quality and reliability: Validate data sources and maintain accuracy in all reports and dashboards.
- Tell the story with data: Present insights through compelling visualisations and narratives that are easy to understand for non-technical audiences.
- Shape BI best practices: Contribute to the company’s data-driven culture by identifying opportunities to enhance reporting and analytics processes.
Qualifications & Experience
- Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Analytics, Data Science, IT, or a related field.
- 5+ years’ experience in business intelligence, insights, or analytics with a proven ability to influence business outcomes.
- Strong experience with BI tools such as Power BI (preferred), Tableau, or Qlik.
- Excellent SQL skills, with proven experience troubleshooting queries, identifying data gaps, and improving query performance.
- Familiarity with Snowflake and AWS cloud-based data warehouses is a strong advantage.
- Ability to go beyond dashboards to deliver insight-led recommendations.
- Excellent communication skills, with the ability to translate complex analysis into business-friendly language.
- A naturally curious mindset with strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
What We Offer
- Opportunity to work closely with senior leadership and shape strategic business decisions.
- Exposure to a wide range of business functions and data sets.
- Competitive salary and benefits package.
- A supportive and innovative work environment where your insights will directly influence outcomes.

Sydney International Airport

dnata Airport Services Australia are excited to announce a new opportunity for a  Business Analyst (Change Focus)  to join our dynamic Projects Team. In this role, you will report directly to the Manager – Strategic Projects.

The Business Analyst (Change Focus) role will be responsible for working with change managers, project teams, and business stakeholders to ensure the successful delivery of new systems, processes, and organisational shifts. Your analytical mindset, communication skills, and curiosity will play a key role in identifying change impacts, supporting planning, and driving alignment across the business.

-  Track change adoption progress, gather user feedback, and identify early signs of resistance. 
-  Maintain change logs, risk registers, and progress reports for visibility and accountability. 
-  Create tailored communications (emails, decks, intranet content) for different stakeholder groups. 
-  Coordinate meetings, workshops, and training to ensure alignment and buy-in. 
-  Support the documentation of new processes, SOPs, user guides, and training materials for new systems or processes. 
-  Analyze performance and adoption data; prepare reports and dashboards to support leadership decision-making and ensure alignment with KPIs. 

Key Qualifications & Experience: 

-  1–2 years’ experience in a Business Analyst, Change Analyst, or Junior Project Analyst role. 
-  Exposure to change management methodologies such as ADKAR, Kotter, or Prosci. 
-  Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to interpret data and translate it into meaningful actions. 
-  Clear and concise written and verbal communication skills. 
- Ability to document workflows, system changes, and training content.
-  Collaborative mindset with strong relationship-building skills across all levels of the business. 
-  Well-organised with the ability to juggle multiple tasks and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment.

Founded in the Queensland outback in 1920, Qantas has grown to be Australia’s largest regional, domestic, and international airline. The Qantas Group’s main business is the transportation of customers and freight using two complementary airline brands — Qantas and Jetstar — operating regional, domestic, and international services.

Job Description

- Challenge yourself to an exciting career within the Qantas Group
-  Together we’ll achieve complete analysis of planning support 
- A 12-months secondment role located at the Qantas Supply Chain

Our ability to stand the test of time has been no coincidence. We’ve come this far because we continue to evolve. It’s a challenge that never ends and drives every individual in our team to make tomorrow better than today for our customers.

Qantas Engineering keeps us at the forefront of aviation, caring and maintaining both the Qantas fleet, as well as aircraft for our customers across the Asia-Pacific region. Working with state-of-the-art equipment and resources, our shared commitment to professional excellence continues to keep our customers safe.

As a Principal Planning Analyst - Components, you will lead a small team in the management of parts under contract that support the Qantas mainline fleet, ensuring contracted part availability targets are met to support On-Time Performance (OTP). This involves managing parts that are contract and modification. You will also monitor supplier performance by working with stakeholders to resolve shortages and improve reliability, as well as contribute to improvement initiatives such as system upgrades and fleet modification programs.

This role is a mix of hands-on supply chain operations and contracted supplier engagement, requiring strong analytical skills, process discipline, and the ability to collaborate across Qantas Engineering and with external suppliers.

You’ll have –

- Experience in supply chain planning, purchasing or inventory management
- Minimum 5 years’ experience in demand planning and inventory optimisation
- Strong understanding of planning, purchasing, and inventory control principles
- Confident using a variety of computer systems, particularly inventory planning tools, Microsoft Excel, and Access
- Excellent verbal and written communication skills
- Proven ability to build and maintain relationships at senior levels, with a strong stakeholder management approach
- Demonstrated leadership capabilities, including experience managing and leading teams
- Strong analytical and financial acumen, with effective problem-solving skills
- A proactive mindset with a focus on continuous improvement

Why Qantas? 

You’ll join a team where creativity and passion are encouraged. Our people come together to allow us to dream big and deliver successfully.

There are many different opportunities across our team, which means you’ll be able to grow both personally and professionally at Qantas. Your development is a priority for us – so that you can maintain the high standards our customers have come to expect and can continue to develop over time. You’ll be supported from day 1 with on-the-job training and coaching as well as our formal training opportunities. While you may start in this role, we’ve got a great track record of supporting our people to take their career in so many different directions, the destinations are endless. 

The Qantas employee benefits program offers amazing benefits that extend well beyond travel. 

- We love to travel: Enjoy heavily discounted air travel within Australia and across the globe, both for you and your family and friends, as well as exclusive deals on accommodation and holidays.
- We have flexible leave options: Make use of leave and flexible working opportunities including 18 weeks paid parental leave and the option to purchase additional paid leave for eligible employees. 
- We’ll give you access to thousands of rewards: Through our partnerships we can offer you discounts across shopping, food and wine, insurance, health and wellbeing, leisure and entertainment. You can also take advantage of our salary packaging program including motor vehicles, eligible portable electronic devices and professional memberships.

-  Identifying opportunities for improvement across the supply chain and providing actionable insights.

- Experience in Replenishment/Forecasting within an FMCG environment.

- Ability to leverage data-driven insights to inform and drive strategic decision-making within a dynamic business environment. 
- Exceptional ability to engage with and support stakeholders and the ability to convey technical ideas to relevant business stakeholders. 
- Experience in SAP S/4 HANA and forecasting modules is an advantage. 
- Collaborative problem-solver, with an analytical, process and technical driven approach to root cause analysis. 

What's in it for you?

Join Australia's fastest growing education franchisor. We offer personalised English and Math tutoring services for K-12 students. We believe in the power of motivating students which has yielded exceptional results across all our students! Join our HQ in coaching and mentoring our existing franchise partners across VIC!

ROLE

- Lead regular online and face-to-face meetings with franchise partners and provide business coaching!
- Provide feedback to HQ on ways to improve business operations and systems
- Liaise with other teams within the HQ to support franchise partners and grow their business
- Regularly review KPIs and set goals for franchise partners to reach
- Follow franchise brand and operational guidelines to ensure that the franchise is consistent

REMUNERATION

- Casual position
- $30 - $34 per hour + Super

Requirements

WHO IS THIS FOR?

- Someone who lives in Melbourne with a passion for business coaching
- Someone who has a car and license to travel to multiple sites across Melbourne
- Great opportunity for University Students who have a passion for Business Consulting!

Habitat Energy is a fast growing technology company focussed on the physical and financial optimisation of energy storage and renewable generation assets globally through complex models and trading. By maximising the returns from these assets we aim to drive investment in renewable energy and accelerate the transition to a low carbon world. Our rapidly growing team of 110+ people in Austin, TX, Oxford, UK, and Melbourne, Australia brings together exceptionally talented and passionate people in the domains of energy trading, data science, software engineering and renewable energy management.

We have a vacancy for a Business Analyst to join our team in Melbourne. This role is crucial to ensuring the requirements of our commercial teams, principally traders, are accurately captured, defined, and translated into actionable insights for our technical teams. Your work will directly influence the profitability and efficiency of our trading strategies by ensuring our technology is perfectly aligned with commercial needs. You will act as a collaborative partner, fostering seamless communication and alignment by bringing together the fast-paced world of energy trading and our software development lifecycle. Working closely with commercial and technical leads you’ll help to shape the product roadmap and ensure user stories are centrally tracked in a clear and concise fashion ready for development. This is a great fit for someone with experience in a business analysis or requirements engineering role who is comfortable in a highly dynamic commercial environment and skilled at translating complex user needs into technical specifications.

You’ll Play a Key Role In

- Bringing together our commercial trading team and our technical delivery teams.
- Leading requirements gathering sessions with traders and other commercial stakeholders to deeply understand their needs, workflows, and pain points.
- Translating commercial needs into clear, well-defined user stories, acceptance criteria, and functional specifications understood by the technology team.
- Contributing to the product roadmap, ensuring captured requirements align with business strategy and are effectively prioritised, with an opportunity to grow into a leadership role in this area.
- Supporting the agile delivery process by clarifying requirements, answering questions from the technical delivery team, encouraging communication and user involvement, and facilitating direct collaboration of tech & users throughout the build phase.
- Analysing and validating that the solutions developed meet the original business objectives and user requirements.
- Managing stakeholder expectations by ensuring clear and consistent communication between all parties.

You Will Be Responsible For

- Partnering with the commercial team to define and articulate their technology requirements.
- Creating and maintaining a clear and organised backlog of user & functional requirements, primarily through user stories in JIRA.
- Ensuring that business context and the "why" behind a requirement are clearly communicated across the commercial and technical delivery teams.
- Working closely with the commercial team to understand requirements originating from external customers.
- Facilitating workshops and interviews to elicit detailed requirements from users.
- Ensuring alignment between the commercial stakeholders and the technical delivery team on the scope and definition of a given feature or project.
- Promoting transparent communication across teams, ensuring that expectations, dependencies, and priorities are well understood.
- Providing updates to ensure transparency and alignment of requirements and outcomes within projects. 

Preferred Skills And Experience

- Proven experience as a Business Analyst, or in a similar role where you were responsible for gathering and defining user requirements for software development.
- Experience working closely with a commercial or business-focused team, such as traders, sales, or account managers.
- Expertise with agile development methodologies and workflow management tools, particularly JIRA.
- Experience with roadmapping tools like ProductBoard is highly advantageous.
- Exceptional communication, collaboration, and stakeholder management skills, with an ability to translate between technical and non-technical audiences.
- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a talent for breaking down complex problems into manageable components.
- Self-motivated, detail-oriented, and able to work independently in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
- Evidence of being able to successfully navigate competing priorities and manage the expectations of demanding stakeholders.
- A technical background or experience working directly with software development 

‘Nice To Have’ Skills And Experience

- Experience working in the energy, finance, or commodities trading sector.
- Business Analysis certifications.

Ultimately we are looking for someone who is a great fit for our company so we encourage you to apply even if you may not meet every requirement in this posting. We value diversity and our environment is supportive, challenging and focused on the consistent delivery of high quality, meaningful work.

Ultimately we are looking for someone who is a great fit for our company so we encourage you to apply even if you may not meet every requirement in this posting. We value diversity and our environment is supportive, challenging and focused on the consistent delivery of high quality, meaningful work.

In return, we’ll give you a competitive salary, flexible working arrangements and a lot of personal development opportunities. We operate a hybrid working model with some time requirement in our office in Melbourne. This role is ideally suited for a part-time arrangement, though full-time applicants will also be considered.

When you apply for a job with us, we process some of your personal information. You can find out more about how we process your information in our candidate privacy policy, here.

Are you passionate about uncovering insights hidden within complex datasets? As a Data Analyst at Easygo, you’ll play a vital role in transforming raw data into actionable intelligence that drives decision-making across our business. This is your chance to shape the future of online entertainment by empowering teams with data-driven strategies and solutions.
What's in it for you?
At Easygo, data sits at the heart of every decision we make. In this role, you’ll have the opportunity to work with large-scale, real-time datasets in a fast-paced and innovative environment. You’ll gain exposure to advanced tools and technologies, collaborate with cross-functional teams, and see your work directly influence business growth and strategy.
Your role with us:
As a Data Analyst at Easygo, you’ll transform raw data into meaningful insights that drive smarter business decisions. You’ll design and automate reports, build dashboards, and dive deep into analysis to uncover trends that shape strategy across compliance, operations, and gaming. Collaborating closely with the Business Intelligence team and stakeholders across the business, you’ll play a key role in making data more accessible, reliable, and impactful.
Who are we?
At Easygo we proudly stand as a prominent service provider to a powerhouse of brands within the entertainment industry, including Stake.com, Kick.com and Twist Gaming. 
Stake is the world's largest crypto casino, and leads the industry with a seamless online casino and sportsbook experience.
Level up your online entertainment with Kick.com, the vibrant live-streaming platform, which connects millions of gamers and content creators worldwide.
All alongside the innovative game design studio, Twist Gaming, which takes creativity to new heights by crafting cutting-edge and captivating games. 
Our commitment to placing our clients and their communities' entertainment at the forefront of everything we do, has solidified us as the ultimate online service provider for entertainment companies.
Headquartered in the beautiful city of Melbourne, our growth has been remarkable. From humble beginnings to a thriving workforce of 600+, we've expanded not only in numbers but in ambition. There really is something for everyone here, whether you work in Tech, Marketing, Operations, Mathematics or Design, we are sure to have something for everyone.
Click play, on your career today!
What you will do: 

- Collect, clean, and analyse large, complex datasets to uncover actionable insights.
- Build and maintain reusable data models that support reporting and analytics at scale.
- Design and automate reports that help stakeholders make informed business decisions.
- Create and manage interactive dashboards that provide visibility into performance and trends.
- Identify and resolve data quality issues, ensuring accuracy and reliability.
- Translate raw data into clear insights that guide strategy across Compliance, Operations, and Gaming.
- Respond to ad-hoc analysis requests from cross-functional teams with clear and concise outputs.
- Contribute to the improvement of data workflows, documentation, and processes.
- Support the development of scalable data integration and visualisation solutions.
- Stay curious and up to date with industry trends, tools, and technologies to continuously enhance our data capabilities.
What you will bring: 

- 2–3 years’ experience in data analysis, statistical modelling, or predictive analytics.
- Strong SQL and Python skills for manipulating, analysing, and interpreting data.
- Hands-on experience with data visualisation tools (e.g. Tableau) to build clear, impactful dashboards.
- Proficiency in ETL processes and tools, such as Databricks, AWS Glue, or equivalent technologies.
- Ability to explain technical findings in a simple, compelling way to non-technical stakeholders.
- Familiarity with machine learning concepts or applications (a bonus, but not essential).
- A proactive mindset comfortable working in a fast-paced environment with shifting priorities.
- A passion for turning complex data into insights that influence big decisions.
Bonus points if you also have:

- Sports & Gambling industry knowledge is advantageous
- Cryptocurrency industry knowledge would be advantageous
- Proficient with Google Suite (Drive, Spreadsheets, Docs) as well as Slack and Jira
Some of the perks of working with us:
Office Perks & Environment

- In-house baristas serving free coffee, tea, fresh juices, and smoothies
- Daily catered breakfast and regular company-wide events
- Snack walls and drink fridges on every floor
- Fun /modern office spaces with pool tables, table tennis, gaming consoles, and an F1 simulator
Wellbeing & Personal Development

- Access to our Employee Assistance Program for you and your loved ones
- 9,000+ courses on our Learning & Development platform
- One paid volunteer day per year
- Weekly Wednesday massages by professional masseuses
Team Connection & Rewards

- Team budgets for lunches and activities to celebrate achievements
- Social sports teams and participation in Corporate Games
- Easygo branded swag
- Birthday and work anniversary gift vouchers, plus a chance to win prizes 
Events & Experiences

- Company-wide talks with key partners such as Everton FC and Team Sauber in Formula 1
- Office visits from big-name streamers
- Meet Ambassadors like Alex Pereira, Israel Adesanya
- Ballots for exclusive tickets to events like Formula 1, UFC, and more sporting and music events
We believe that the unique contributions of everyone at Easygo are the driver of our success. To make sure that our products and culture continue to incorporate everyone's perspectives and experiences, we never discriminate on the basis of race, religion, nationality, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status. 
We’re a global team of dreamers, creators, and game-changers from every walk of life, united by a passion for entertainment that inspires the world.
We believe that the best ideas come from different perspectives, so we actively welcome and champion talent from all backgrounds, cultures, identities, and experiences. Whether you're just starting out or bringing decades of experience, your unique voice matters here.
